g.aria-label: Portion of species lost from 1900 to 2014Documented rates of species loss from 1900 to 2014, together with expected loss under an estimatedbackground rate (i.e. the natural rate absent human activity) of 0.02% per century. Source:Ceballos et al..Ceballos, G., Ehrlich, P., Barnosky, A., García, A., Pringle, R., Palmer, T. "Accelerated modern human–induced species losses:Entering the sixth mass extinction". Science Advances1(5), e1400253.June 2015.
